    "body": "I am encountering a problem when I use the conda module that may be related to this, using:\r\n```\r\nstarship 1.13.1\r\nbranch:\r\ncommit_hash:\r\nbuild_time:2023-02-26 01:47:34 +00:00\r\nbuild_env:rustc 1.67.1 (d5a82bbd2 2023-02-07) (built from a source tarball),\r\n```\r\non macOS Ventura 13.3.\r\n\r\nWhen my prompt is almost the full width of my terminal window, line wrapping in the terminal fails. What I observe is that typing a long command will cause the cursor to return to the start of the current line, rather than going on to a new line. If I remove the conda module from my `format` statement, the problem goes away. This may be because of an incorrect calculation of the length of the prompt when the conda module is active.\r\n\r\nI’m not sure how to provide better debugging information, but would be happy to help by answering any questions or performing some tests in my machine.",
